# QA Agent Workflow Routing

Use `AGENTS.md` and `.github/agents/` as the source of truth for AI-agent QA work.

Route work as follows:

- Test planning: `.github/agents/playwright-test-planner.agent.md`
- Playwright test writing: `.github/agents/playwright-test-generator.agent.md`
- Failed test debugging/fixing: `.github/agents/playwright-test-healer.agent.md`
- Framework implementation: `.github/agents/framework-engineer.agent.md`
- CI repair/improvement: `.github/agents/cicd-repair.agent.md`
- Flakiness reduction: `.github/agents/stability-flakiness.agent.md`
- Performance optimization: `.github/agents/performance-agent.agent.md`
- Test/framework review: `.github/agents/playwright-test-reviewer.agent.md`
- Final verification: `.github/agents/verification-agent.agent.md`

Reusable workflow prompts live in `.github/prompts/`.

Always keep `specs/` and `tests/` synchronized:

- Plans need stable `Plan ID` values and `Automation` lines.
- Generated specs need top-of-file `// spec:` and `// plan-id:` comments.
- Run `npm run plan-coverage` before reporting automation work complete.

Do not hide failures with skips, deleted tests, weakened assertions, arbitrary waits, or undocumented retries.

For linked GitHub issues, never close or report the issue complete after local validation alone. The fix must be
committed, pushed, and verified by green GitHub Actions for the pushed commit first.
